profile_positions.description:
Supporting the Department Director of Product planning and Research & Development for research and planning in various areas.

I'm responsible for:
– daily systematic research, collection, analysis and organization of the European Market information data in miscellaneous areas. My work is useful to several Japanese departments (like R&D dept., Product planning dept. Marketing dept. etc.);
– regular production of reports and presentations which helps Japanese employees to better understand the needs and the structure of the European market in the different European countries. Based on my dedicated investigations, engineers, developers and designers are able to point out specific marketing strategies; 
– arranging any practical part of research activities and web survey;
– preparing market researches activities and concept/styling clinics;
– invoicing the expenses (international invoicing using Xtendis);
– purchasing and sending competitive models and parts for references of development;
– keeping any information about under-development products confidentially outside of R&D dept.;
– keeping all information, data files and structural magazines in R&D share drive and archive.

For this role I deepened into different aspects of the following skills: research, data analysis, reporting, international relations, export documentation, international documentation and administration.

In this ambitious start-up I held various roles carrying out a huge number of duties.
• As Product Owner and Scrum Master I was:
– determining business strategy and establishing the business plan (competitors estimate, marketing 
analysis, etc.);
– developing product and sale strategy;
– managing a team of developers to create and maintain the websites;
– creating the content of our websites;
– the project manager, planning and coordinating the team, basing the activities on priorities 
and producing regular reports to update the Owner on all the projects. 
– set, prioritise, and evaluate the work done by the development team, verifying that it was suitable to all the 
requirements of creating/maintaining/implementing the 
websites (SCRUM / Agile methodology),
– solving the external problems, help the team to achieve goals, 
– retrospectively analyze the work, focussed on resuls and the 
team’s needs.
• As Digital Marketing Specialist I was:
– leading advertisement and sales operations; 
– using GA & AdS to develop marketing strategy for each website & type of client; 
– using marketing communication and social media marketing to create offline & digital advertising 
campaigns with associated objectives such as qualitative traffic or conversions; 
– creating marketing content on social media and on the e-commerce using SEO & SEA;
– setting up and daily updating social media pages (Facebook & Twitter pages customized 
for each website), updating periodically the websites;
– sending DEM & standard newsletters.

As frequently happens in a small company and especially in a start-up, you have to work hard 
and carry out every possible kind of activity you are qualified to do in parallel. That’s why in 
these years I also carried out (fully or partially) the functions of:
• UI, supporting the clients to get the best experience result
• UX, testing the websites on the most common browsers
• Accounting-Administrative Manager

I’ve been working in a development team to test the new corporate website for final EU-wide roll out. 
• I was responsible for:
– writing extensive scenarios based on the user input, the administrator approval and the shipper feedbacks; 
– checking and modifying the scenarios using SAP and Excel for integration testing;
– mimicking user, administrator and supplier usage to optimize functionality and enhance friendliness 
for the ultimate user.

Italiana immobiliare SpA, founded in 1980, is today the most important real estate company in Tuscany: it started in the real estate brokerage sector and then turned into a "service" company, mainly supporting franchising.
As Real Estate Agent I was in charge of:

- searching for any kind of properties to sell or rent;
- carrying out a technical inspection to make an estimate of the market value, and to point out the strong points of the property to better centre the sale strategy;
- informing the customer of the opportunities and of the different kind of contracts and services available;
- supporting the client until the signing of the contract of engagement;
- remaining the contact person for any kind of question and matter until the sale or the rent of the property.
